    memoryTrick: "Primary = original document. Replica = photocopy. Sync = wait for photocopy to finish before saying 'done.' Async = say 'done' and photocopy later.",
    relatedConcepts: ["sharding", "cap-theorem", "replication-strategies", "availability"],
    cheatSheetLine: "Single-leader: simple, write SPOF. Sync: no data loss, slow. Async: fast, replication lag. Quorum W+R>N for leaderless.",
